Body colouration is sometimes interrupted by 5–6 dark, slightly wavy, almost straight, lines on the body of juveniles and adults, although stripes are more prominent in juveniles: first following base of dorsal sheath; second, running from the anterior of nape to below posterior of soft dorsal ray base; third running from posttemporal to dorsal edge of caudal peduncle; fourth, follows the lateral line, starting at anterior base of dorsal fin and ending at posterior base; fifth, from supracleithrum to middle of caudal base; sixth, running between the largest opercular spine and ventral edge of caudal peduncle. Lines generally fade in adults (SL 
70–90 mm
). Lines also fade quickly once fish are removed from the water or after death.
